---
import Base from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCTA from '../../components/EmailCTA.astro';
import { applications } from '../../data/applications';
import { caseStudies } from '../../data/case-studies';
const industries = [
  ['Utility Substations','Power transformer OTI, WTI, cooling and remote monitoring','power-transformer-temperature-monitoring'],
  ['Transformer Manufacturers','Controlled model, drawing and interface selection for production programs','power-transformer-temperature-monitoring'],
  ['Wind and Solar Power','Remote transformer temperature data for renewable-energy substations','substation-remote-temperature-monitoring'],
  ['Hydropower','Top-oil indication, cooling contacts and control-room integration','power-transformer-temperature-monitoring'],
  ['Industrial Distribution','Temperature alarm, cooling and protection coordination','transformer-cooling-control-alarm-trip'],
  ['Retrofit Projects','BWY and BWR replacement based on complete mechanical and electrical data','transformer-temperature-controller-retrofit']
];
const schema={'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'CollectionPage',name:'Oil-Immersed Transformer Temperature Monitoring Applications',description:'Engineering application guidance for transformer oil and winding temperature monitoring across utilities, renewable energy, industry and retrofit projects.'};
---
<Base title="Transformer Temperature Monitoring Applications | INNO" description="Plan oil-immersed transformer temperature monitoring applications for utilities, renewable energy, industrial systems and retrofit projects." schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Oil-immersed transformer environments</p><h1>Transformer Temperature Monitoring Applications</h1><p>Define the operating environment, thermal variable, signal path and installation interface before selecting the monitoring equipment.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block"><strong>Application planning answer.</strong> A transformer temperature monitoring application coordinates the field measurement, local indication, cooling contacts, alarm or trip outputs and remote data path. Product selection follows the transformer design and operating purpose.</div><div class="section-head"><h2>Choose a Transformer Temperature Monitoring Application</h2></div><div class="grid two">{applications.map((item,index)=><article class="card application-card"><a class="application-card-media" href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}><img src={caseStudies[index].image} alt={`${item.title} environment`} width="1600" height="900" loading="lazy"></a><h3><a href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}>{item.title}</a></h3><p>{item.intro}</p></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><div class="container"><div class="section-head"><h2>Industries and Project Environments</h2><p class="lead">Start from the operating environment, then confirm the measured value, control action and installation interface.</p></div><div class="industry-matrix">{industries.map(([title,text,slug])=><article><h3><a href={`/applications/${slug}/`}>{title}</a></h3><p>{text}</p></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="section-head"><h2>Country Application Configurations</h2><p class="lead">Compare environmental conditions, transformer duties, monitoring signals and commissioning requirements.</p></div><div class="case-grid compact">{caseStudies.slice(0,4).map(item=><article class="case-card"><a class="case-card-media" href={`/case-studies/${item.slug}/`}><img src={item.image} alt={`${item.country} transformer monitoring environment`} width="1600" height="900" loading="lazy" style={`object-position:${item.imagePosition}`}></a><div class="case-card-body"><p class="case-country">{item.country}</p><h3><a href={`/case-studies/${item.slug}/`}>{item.title}</a></h3></div></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>What must be defined before selecting the monitoring system?</h2><p>State whether the project needs transformer top-oil temperature, traditionally simulated winding temperature or another direct measurement. Then define the local display, cooling stages, alarm and trip philosophy, remote interface, receiving equipment and commissioning method.</p><h3>Connect OTI and WTI values to the correct operating decision</h3><p>An OTI follows top-oil temperature at a specified thermometer pocket. A WTI adds a load-current-related thermal simulation. Their contacts and remote tags should retain those identities so operators do not treat unlike values as the same temperature.</p><h3>Use application pages to select a product path</h3><p>After reviewing the application, compare <a href="/products/transformer-oil-temperature-indicators/">transformer oil temperature indicators</a>, <a href="/products/transformer-winding-temperature-indicators/">transformer winding temperature indicators</a> and <a href="/products/transformer-temperature-monitoring-devices/">remote monitoring devices</a>.</p></article></section>
  <EmailCTA title="Plan a Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solution" subject="Transformer temperature monitoring application review" />
</Base>
